1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with object detection in aerial imagery using a modified version of the YOLOv2 detector. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper involves the use of deep learning techniques to improve the performance of object detection in aerial imagery. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve the performance of object detection in aerial imagery. This falls under the domain of machine learning. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper involves the use of object detection in aerial imagery, which can be useful in robotics applications such as autonomous drones. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves the use of image processing techniques to retrieve information from aerial imagery, which falls under the domain of information retrieval.
